22/11/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Employees in the education sector launched a three-day strike on Wednesday (November 22nd) demanding a salary hike from the government. Their union says secondary school teachers walked off the job first and will be followed on Thursday by those at primary schools. The cabinet is offering wage hikes of 5% next year. The union notes that the gap between salaries in the educational sector and the private sector exceeds 21%. (HRT, Vjesnik, Vecernji list - 22/11/06; HINA - 21/11/06)
